<#C22PU4LV8|general> Hello everyone!
I am developer using HubSpot Tracking code js.
I have my custom Cookie Consent banner with user can allow/disallow each category cookies to be stored or not.
Based upon users consent I have want to pass consent levels to HubSpot so that HubSpot stores cookies according to provided consent level instead of loading all categories cookies.
Can anyone help on on this ? OR suggest specific channel where i can ask for help.
Thanks !

Hello everyone would just like to ask if anyone has had to manage over 200 workflows. One of the criteria for a job I was asked to consider said they need someone to manage 200 workflows and create more. This isn’t big company so it struck me as very odd. Thoughts?
I got about 450 workflows with 250ish on right now.  Do you know what they are doing with workflows? Maybe they break out workflows on an individual basis and not grouped.
Hi Chris, can you submit this to the in-app support? They should be able to assist with looking into this.
<@U2H3TT8F2>, we did open a Support ticket but they currently have not be able to assist us
I didn’t get that far in our conversation. Thanks for the feedback.
how can a developer test calling using twilio? it says i "need a sales hub account". don't i have one as a dev?

<@U2H3TT8F2> so Support and our Tech consult is saying that /hubfs paths are not allowed for redirect pages but what would be a viable solution if we do not want a File that was deleted from File Manager to not 404, and actually get redirected to a webpage, like if it was a Legal PDF and now we have a Legal page to represent that? what would be your solution to solve this issue?
Gotcha, depending how they use them could be but I would not see it as a red flag from my end. Marketing workflows, sales, customer service it all can add up.
